goals.question: What is the relationship between flipper length and body mass?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='Species', y='Beak_Length__mm_', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of beak length across different penguin species?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Penguin Species')
    plt.ylabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[data['Sex'].isin(['MALE', 'FEMALE'])]
    male_penguins = data[data['Sex'] == 'MALE']
    female_penguins = data[data['Sex'] == 'FEMALE']

    plt.hist(male_penguins['Body_Mass__g_'], alpha=0.5, label='Male', color='blue')
    plt.hist(female_penguins['Body_Mass__g_'], alpha=0.5, label='Female', color='red')

    plt.xlabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('How does the body mass of male and female penguins compare?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Flipper_Length__mm_'], data['Body_Mass__g_'], c=data['Species'].cat.codes, cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Flipper Length (mm)')
    plt.ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between flipper length and body mass?', wrap=True)
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Species")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='Beak_Depth__mm_', by='Island', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of beak depth across different islands?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Island')
    ax.set_ylabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend(title='Island', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    island_mean_mass = data.groupby('Island')['Body_Mass__g_'].mean()
    ax = island_mean_mass.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green'])
    plt.title('How does the body mass of penguins vary across different islands?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Island')
    plt.ylabel('Average Body Mass (g)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax.legend(["Average Body Mass"])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
